messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /cms/admin/user/{uid}

All methods acceptable:
- No

Methods allowed (based on the code):
- HEAD: No
- POST: No
- OPTIONS: No
- TRACE: No
- GET: No
- PUT: Yes
- DELETE: Yes
- PATCH: No

Explanation:
- Blueprints and prefixes: create_app registers the cms blueprint with url_prefix "/cms" (app/__init__.py). The cms blueprint (app/api/cms/__init__.py) registers admin_api with url_prefix "/admin". The delete_user route is defined in app/api/cms/admin.py on admin_api as @admin_api.route("/user/<int:uid>", methods=["DELETE"]). Combining the prefixes yields /cms + /admin + /user/{uid} â†’ /cms/admin/user/{uid}.
- Explicit methods in code: The delete_user function is decorated with methods=["DELETE"], so DELETE is allowed. The same path is also registered for update_user with methods=["PUT"], so PUT is allowed on that full path too.
- No other route in the provided code registers this exact path for GET, POST, PATCH, or TRACE, so those are not allowed per the code.
- HEAD and OPTIONS are not explicitly declared in the route decorators. Per the instructions to base acceptance on the code (not on framework runtime behavior), they are reported as not acceptable.
